#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:1
msgid "E0017"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `ambiguous_loop_argument`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:5
msgid ""
"The usage of identifier is ambiguous. If it refers to the loop variable, "
"please use `as <id>` to bind it in the pattern. If it refers to the "
"original value of the variable before entering the loop, please bind it "
"to a new binder outside the loop."
msgstr ""
"标识符的使用存在歧义。如果它指的是循环变量，请使用 `as <id>` "
"在模式中绑定它。如果它指的是变量在进入循环前的原始值，请在循环外部将其绑定到一个新的绑定器。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:10
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr "错误示例"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:12
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"fn main {\n"
"  let a : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
"  loop a {\n"
"    [_, .. d] => {\n"
"      println(a)\n"
"      //      ^\n"
"      // Warning: The usage of 'a' is ambiguous. If it refers to the loop"
"\n"
"      // variable, please use `as a` to bind it in the pattern. If it "
"refers to\n"
"      // the original value of 'a' before entering the loop, please bind "
"it to a\n"
"      // new binder outside the loop.\n"
"      continue d\n"
"    }\n"
"    [] => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:20
#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:52
#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:68
msgid "Output:"
msgstr "输出："

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:22
#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:70
msgid ""
"asdf\n"
"asdf\n"
"asdf\n"
"asdf\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:25
msgid ""
"Because `a` refers to the value of `a` before entering the loop, "
"therefore the value is always the same."
msgstr "因为 `a` 指的是进入循环前的 `a` 的值，因此该值始终相同。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:28
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr "建议"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:30
msgid ""
"Since `loop` syntax will be removed soon, prefer rewriting new code with "
"a `for` loop when possible. For example, this code can be written as:"
msgstr ""
"由于 `loop` 语法很快会被移除，若条件允许，建议优先将新代码改写为 `for` 循环。例如，这段代码可以写成："

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:33
msgid ""
"let text : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
"for i = 0; i < text.length(); i = i + 1 {\n"
"  println(text[i:])\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:40
msgid ""
"If you are maintaining existing `loop` code, and you want to refer to the"
" loop variable that changes with loop iterations, use `as <id>` to bind "
"it in the pattern."
msgstr ""
"如果你是在维护现有的 `loop` 代码，并且想引用随循环迭代而变化的循环变量，请使用 `as <id>` 在模式中绑定它。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:44
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"fn main {\n"
"  let a : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
"  loop a {\n"
"    [_, .. d] as a => {\n"
"      println(a)\n"
"      continue d\n"
"    }\n"
"    [] => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:54
msgid ""
"asdf\n"
"sdf\n"
"df\n"
"f\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:57
msgid ""
"Or, if you want to refer to the original value of the variable before "
"entering the loop, explicitly bind it to another name outside the loop."
msgstr "或者，如果你想在进入循环之前引用变量的原始值，可以显式地将其绑定到循环外的另一个名称。"

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0017.md:60
msgid ""
"///|\n"
"fn main {\n"
"  let a : StringView = \"asdf\"\n"
"  let b = a\n"
"  loop a {\n"
"    [_, .. d] => {\n"
"      println(b)\n"
"      continue d\n"
"    }\n"
"    [] => ()\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
